*** Sass ***

(Syntactically Awesome Stylesheets)

http://sass-lang.com/

Is a stylesheet language.

scss y sass (older)

Features:

1. Variables
2. Nesting
3. Mixins
4. Selector inheritance

Using sass out of ruby projects

INSTALLATION

$> gem install sass
$> sass --watch views/stylesheets/application.sass:public/stylesheets/application.css

__FILE__ views/stylesheets/application.sass

$blue:#3bbfce

@mixin left($dist)
  float: left
  margin-left: $dist
  padding-left: $dist/2
  
table
  @include left(10)
  th
    color: $blue

.board
  width: 500px
  height: 500px

.user-board
  @extend .board  
  border-color: $blue

.opponent-board
  @extend .board
  border-color: red

__EOFILE__

link rel="stylesheet" href="stylesheets/applications.css"

*** Compass ***

http://compass-style.org/

gem install compass

__FILE__ config.rb

http_path = "/"

css_dir = "stylesheets"
javascripts_dir = "javascripts"
images_dir = "images"

sass_dir = "views/stylesheets"

preferred_syntax = :sass

__EOF__

$> compass watch . (or path/to/project not to file, do not run with sass --watch)

Features:

